#. [message]
#: .\scenarios\chapter5\35_Scavengers_Trading_Post.cfg:2031
msgid ""
"It looks like it has been corrupted, like the ones we encountered in the "
"swamp. But this time, the corruption feels... natural."
msgstr ""

#. [message]
#: .\scenarios\chapter5\35_Scavengers_Trading_Post.cfg:2035
msgid ""
"There must be some kind of mad wose in this forest corrupting neighboring "
"trees."
msgstr ""

#. [message], speaker=second_unit
#: .\scenarios\chapter5\35_Scavengers_Trading_Post.cfg:2047
msgid "It looks like that tree was completely rotten."
msgstr ""

#. [message]
#: .\scenarios\chapter5\35_Scavengers_Trading_Post.cfg:2051
msgid ""
"It must have been the mad wose that corrupted all the other trees. The forest"
" should be more peaceful now."
msgstr ""

#. [message]
#: .\scenarios\chapter5\35_Scavengers_Trading_Post.cfg:2055
msgid "Well, I mean, apart from the rest of the wildlife trying to kill us."
msgstr ""

#. [message], speaker=unit
#: .\scenarios\chapter5\35_Scavengers_Trading_Post.cfg:2068
msgid "There was a cyclops in the house."
msgstr ""

#. [message], speaker=unit
#: .\scenarios\chapter5\35_Scavengers_Trading_Post.cfg:2087
msgid "There are stairs going down into a tunnel."
msgstr ""

#. [message], speaker=Io
#: .\scenarios\chapter5\35_Scavengers_Trading_Post.cfg:2097
msgid "It must be the flooded tunnels Oboavlidlu told us about."
msgstr ""

#. [message], speaker=unit
#: .\scenarios\chapter5\35_Scavengers_Trading_Post.cfg:2101
#: .\scenarios\chapter5\35_Scavengers_Trading_Post.cfg:2140
msgid "Should we go down there?"
msgstr ""

#. [option]
#: .\scenarios\chapter5\35_Scavengers_Trading_Post.cfg:2103
msgid ""
"Yes, we should try to find the treasure hunters. Who knows what happened to "
"them?"
msgstr ""

#. [option]
#: .\scenarios\chapter5\35_Scavengers_Trading_Post.cfg:2131
#: .\scenarios\chapter5\35_Scavengers_Trading_Post.cfg:2170
msgid "No, we have no time for that. We need to go down the old temple road."
msgstr ""

#. [option]
#: .\scenarios\chapter5\35_Scavengers_Trading_Post.cfg:2142
msgid "Yes, let's see where it leads."
msgstr ""

#. [message], speaker=Io
#: .\scenarios\chapter5\35_Scavengers_Trading_Post.cfg:2188
msgid "Let's continue. We need to reach Oof's fortress as quickly as possible."
msgstr ""

#. [message], speaker=Io
#: .\scenarios\chapter5\35_Scavengers_Trading_Post.cfg:2202
msgid "How many walking trees are there in this forest?!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]
#: .\scenarios\chapter5\35_Scavengers_Trading_Post.cfg:2211
msgid "There are a lot of trees, but not all of them are wose."
msgstr ""

#. [message]
#: .\scenarios\chapter5\35_Scavengers_Trading_Post.cfg:2215
msgid ""
"On the plus side, as you have seen, the wose are quite slow, so we just need "
"to progress faster than they are coming for us."
msgstr ""

#. [message]
#: .\scenarios\chapter5\35_Scavengers_Trading_Post.cfg:2219
msgid ""
"Even better, if we could get rid of the wose that is spreading the corruption"
" to the forest, the trees should then leave us in peace."
msgstr ""

#. [scenario], id=36_Old_Temple_Road
#: .\scenarios\chapter5\36_Old_Temple_Road.cfg:4
msgid "Old Temple Road"
msgstr ""

#. [objective], condition=win
#: .\scenarios\chapter5\36_Old_Temple_Road.cfg:36
msgid "Find the entrance of the old temple"
msgstr ""

#. [side], type=Deathlord LotI
#: .\scenarios\chapter5\36_Old_Temple_Road.cfg:598
msgid "Undead Leader"
msgstr ""

#. [message], speaker=Io
#: .\scenarios\chapter5\36_Old_Temple_Road.cfg:644
msgid "The road seems to continue north. I assume the temple is in the forest."
msgstr ""

#. [message]
#: .\scenarios\chapter5\36_Old_Temple_Road.cfg:648
msgid "From what I recall, it is actually in a clearing."
msgstr ""

#. [message]
#: .\scenarios\chapter5\36_Old_Temple_Road.cfg:652
msgid "Then I will be glad when we get out of this forest. It is oppressing."
msgstr ""

#. [message]
#: .\scenarios\chapter5\36_Old_Temple_Road.cfg:671
msgid "Undead. What a surprise."
msgstr ""

#. [message]
#: .\scenarios\chapter5\36_Old_Temple_Road.cfg:675
msgid "It is not like we were supposed to go fight a powerful necromancer."
msgstr ""

#. [message]
#: .\scenarios\chapter5\36_Old_Temple_Road.cfg:679
msgid "At least, we know it is the right way..."
msgstr ""

#. [message], speaker=Io
#: .\scenarios\chapter5\36_Old_Temple_Road.cfg:683
msgid ""
"Let's try not to keep any undead behind us. I'm already afraid that they will"
" warn Isut about us, I would rather not have them attack us in the back at "
"the worst time."
msgstr ""

#. [objective], condition=win
#: .\scenarios\chapter5\36_Old_Temple_Road.cfg:688
msgid "Find the entrance of the Old Temple"
msgstr ""

#. [objective], condition=win
#: .\scenarios\chapter5\36_Old_Temple_Road.cfg:693
msgid "Kill all undead"
msgstr ""

#. [message], speaker=narrator
#: .\scenarios\chapter5\36_Old_Temple_Road.cfg:720
msgid ""
"South-east: The Scavenger’s Trading Post\n"
"North: Oof's Fortress"
msgstr ""

#. [message], speaker=unit
#: .\scenarios\chapter5\36_Old_Temple_Road.cfg:744
msgid "Look! It looks like the entrance of the Old Temple is here."
msgstr ""

#. [message], speaker=Io
#: .\scenarios\chapter5\36_Old_Temple_Road.cfg:764
msgid "We don't have more time to waste here. Let's go!"
msgstr ""

#. [message], speaker=Io
#: .\scenarios\chapter5\36_Old_Temple_Road.cfg:768
msgid "We need to reach Oof's fortress before captain Soimaql get overwhelmed."
msgstr ""

#. [message], speaker=Io
#: .\scenarios\chapter5\36_Old_Temple_Road.cfg:772
msgid ""
"I'm a bit afraid of the tentacle guardians we were warned about, let's hope "
"we can cross without meeting them."
msgstr ""

#. [message], speaker=Io
#: .\scenarios\chapter5\36_Old_Temple_Road.cfg:784
#: .\scenarios\chapter5\38_Isut.cfg:929
msgid "Wait for us! We are still fighting the undead here!"
msgstr ""

#. [message], speaker=Io
#: .\scenarios\chapter5\36_Old_Temple_Road.cfg:806
msgid "I don't see any more undead around here. I think we can continue safely."
msgstr ""

#. [message], speaker=Io
#: .\scenarios\chapter5\36_Old_Temple_Road.cfg:810
msgid ""
"Well, I mean, as safely as we can with a necromancer and tentacle monsters on"
" our way."
msgstr ""

#. [message], speaker=Io
#: .\scenarios\chapter5\36_Old_Temple_Road.cfg:814
msgid "Let's get into the Old Temple."
msgstr ""

#. [message], speaker=Io
#: .\scenarios\chapter5\36_Old_Temple_Road.cfg:830
msgid "I think we are lost. We should have stayed on the main road."
msgstr ""

#. [message], speaker=Io
#: .\scenarios\chapter5\36_Old_Temple_Road.cfg:834
msgid "Now, we will arrive too late to save captain Soimaql, and the kingdom."
msgstr ""

#. [scenario], id=37_Old_Temple
#: .\scenarios\chapter5\37_Old_Temple.cfg:4
msgid "Old Temple"
msgstr ""

#. [objective], condition=win
#: .\scenarios\chapter5\37_Old_Temple.cfg:30
msgid "Cross the old temple"
msgstr ""

#. [objective], condition=win
#: .\scenarios\chapter5\37_Old_Temple.cfg:35
msgid "Defeat both enemy leaders"
msgstr ""

#. [objectives]
#: .\scenarios\chapter5\37_Old_Temple.cfg:48
msgid "Petrification can be healed in this scenario."
msgstr ""

#. [side], type=Fury LoI
#. [unit_type], id=Fury LoI, race=demon-loti, gender=female
#: .\scenarios\chapter5\37_Old_Temple.cfg:104
#: .\units\Fury.cfg:4
msgid "Fury"
msgstr ""

#. [side], type=Mine Worm LoI
#: .\scenarios\chapter5\37_Old_Temple.cfg:120
msgid "Worms"
msgstr ""

#. [message], speaker=Io
#: .\scenarios\chapter5\37_Old_Temple.cfg:431
msgid ""
"So, this is the Old Temple. It looks like it was once majestic. But now it's "
"just... old"
msgstr ""

#. [message], speaker=Io
#: .\scenarios\chapter5\37_Old_Temple.cfg:435
msgid ""
"Anyway, we need to cross it to reach Oof's fortress and save Captain Soimaql."
" We must expect to have to fight a ``tentacle monster'', although I have no "
"idea what it might encompass."
msgstr ""

#. [message], speaker=Io
#: .\scenarios\chapter5\37_Old_Temple.cfg:439
msgid "And undead. Undead too. Why not undead, indeed?..."
msgstr ""

#. [message]
#: .\scenarios\chapter5\37_Old_Temple.cfg:443
msgid ""
"I can feel a strong force of black magic north. There must be a powerful "
"necromancer there."
msgstr ""

#. [message], speaker=Io
#: .\scenarios\chapter5\37_Old_Temple.cfg:447
msgid ""
"If we believe in the reports, Isut must be at the fortress already, meaning "
"it is either one of his lackeys or one of his allies."
msgstr ""

#. [message], speaker=Io
#: .\scenarios\chapter5\37_Old_Temple.cfg:451
msgid ""
"I guess we will find out if we meet them. Although that would probably be a "
"good idea to defeat them: I would rather not have undead behind AND in front "
"of us."
msgstr ""

#. [message], speaker=Io
#: .\scenarios\chapter5\37_Old_Temple.cfg:476
msgid ""
"What's this monstrosity? It is a bit like a Mine Worm, but much bigger and "
"scarier."
msgstr ""

#. [message]
#: .\scenarios\chapter5\37_Old_Temple.cfg:480
msgid "I am afraid it might be a beast called a Mehsi."
msgstr ""

#. [message]
#: .\scenarios\chapter5\37_Old_Temple.cfg:484
msgid "Some scholars theorize it to be the adult form of the Mine Worm."
msgstr ""

#. [message], speaker=Amin
#: .\scenarios\chapter5\37_Old_Temple.cfg:488
msgid ""
"I refuse to believe that! Implying us dwarves have been struggling with mere "
"younglings for generation!"
msgstr ""

#. [message], speaker=Amin
#: .\scenarios\chapter5\37_Old_Temple.cfg:492
msgid "Bloody scholars! Disrespecting the entire dwarvish race."
msgstr ""

#. [message], speaker=Io
#: .\scenarios\chapter5\37_Old_Temple.cfg:496
msgid ""
"Mine Worm or not, be careful everyone, because it looks like it could eat any"
" of us whole. Even a horse..."
msgstr ""

#. [message], speaker=Io
#: .\scenarios\chapter5\37_Old_Temple.cfg:521
msgid ""
"So, this must be the famous tentacle monster. Be careful everyone one, it "
"made the legionary nearly mad."
msgstr ""

#. [message], speaker=Io
#: .\scenarios\chapter5\37_Old_Temple.cfg:537
msgid "Wait, there are two of them?!"
msgstr ""

#. [message], speaker=Io
#: .\scenarios\chapter5\37_Old_Temple.cfg:541
msgid ""
"Or could it be that those are not the tentacle monster and that something "
"even scarier is?"
msgstr ""

#. [message], speaker=Io
#: .\scenarios\chapter5\37_Old_Temple.cfg:565
msgid ""
"Oh! So, this is the tentacle monster! No wonder that poor legionary went mad "
"fleeing that thing."
msgstr ""

#. [message], speaker=Io
#: .\scenarios\chapter5\37_Old_Temple.cfg:569
msgid ""
"Unlucky us, it looks like it's blocking the exit. I'm not sure we will be "
"able to pass without fighting it..."
msgstr ""

#. [message], speaker=necromancer
#: .\scenarios\chapter5\37_Old_Temple.cfg:589
msgid ""
"You may have found me, but you will never be able to defeat Mal Wlicikoyl, "
"Commander Isut's second in command."
msgstr ""

#. [message], speaker=Io
#: .\scenarios\chapter5\37_Old_Temple.cfg:593
msgid "Well, at least we know who we are facing."
msgstr ""

#. [message], speaker=Io
#: .\scenarios\chapter5\37_Old_Temple.cfg:597
msgid ""
"It would be a great victory to defeat him as it would probably impair their "
"undead army."
msgstr ""

#. [message], speaker=necromancer
#: .\scenarios\chapter5\37_Old_Temple.cfg:610
msgid "You may have defeated me, but never will you defeat Commander Isut!"
msgstr ""

#. [message], speaker=second_unit
#: .\scenarios\chapter5\37_Old_Temple.cfg:631
msgid "It looks like all the undead he was commanding are crumbling to dust."
msgstr ""

#. [message]
#: .\scenarios\chapter5\37_Old_Temple.cfg:644
#: .\scenarios\chapter5\37_Old_Temple.cfg:660
msgid "It looks like some undead are still standing."
msgstr ""

#. [message]
#: .\scenarios\chapter5\37_Old_Temple.cfg:648
#: .\scenarios\chapter5\37_Old_Temple.cfg:664
msgid ""
"Those are probably directly controlled by Isut. There should not be many that"
" far from the fortress."
msgstr ""

#. [message], speaker=second_unit
#: .\scenarios\chapter5\37_Old_Temple.cfg:681
msgid "That's it! We defeated the tentacle monster!"
msgstr ""

#. [message], speaker=Io
#: .\scenarios\chapter5\37_Old_Temple.cfg:690
msgid ""
"We might not have defeated the necromancer, but once we will have defeated "
"Isut, it should be easy for the Legion to clean the Temple."
msgstr ""

#. [message], speaker=Io
#: .\scenarios\chapter5\37_Old_Temple.cfg:694
#: .\scenarios\chapter5\37_Old_Temple.cfg:710
msgid "Now, let's get out of here, find this Isut and save Captain Soimaql!"
msgstr ""

#. [message], speaker=Io
#: .\scenarios\chapter5\37_Old_Temple.cfg:706
msgid ""
"Now that we have defeated both the monster and the necromancer, people should"
" be able to use this way again once Isut is defeated."
msgstr ""

#. [objective], condition=win
#: .\scenarios\chapter5\38_Isut.cfg:50
msgid "Defeat Isut"
msgstr ""

#. [objective], condition=win
#: .\scenarios\chapter5\38_Isut.cfg:59
msgid "Enter Oof's fortress"
msgstr ""

#. [objective], condition=win
#: .\scenarios\chapter5\38_Isut.cfg:71
msgid "Defeat all undead"
msgstr ""

#. [unit], id=Isut, type=Demon
#: .\scenarios\chapter5\38_Isut.cfg:137
msgid "Commander Isut"
msgstr ""

#. [side], type=Draug
#: .\scenarios\chapter5\38_Isut.cfg:150
msgid "Undead Hordes"
msgstr ""

#. [side], type=Dwarvish Steelclad
#. [side], type=Duelist
#: .\scenarios\chapter5\38_Isut.cfg:388
#: .\scenarios\chapter6\39_Oofs_Fortress.cfg:94
msgid "Defenders"
msgstr ""

#. [message], speaker=Io
#: .\scenarios\chapter5\38_Isut.cfg:455
msgid "I'm glad to finally be out of this cave. It was oppressing."
msgstr ""

#. [message], speaker=Io
#: .\scenarios\chapter5\38_Isut.cfg:459
msgid "Probably because of how old everything was in there."
msgstr ""

#. [message], speaker=Io
#: .\scenarios\chapter5\38_Isut.cfg:463
msgid "And undead. Undead too. And tentacle monsters."
msgstr ""

#. [message], speaker=Io
#: .\scenarios\chapter5\38_Isut.cfg:467
msgid ""
"Anyway, we must not be far from the fortress now. We need to find Isut "
"quickly and defeat him before the fortress fall."
msgstr ""

#. [message], speaker=narrator
#: .\scenarios\chapter5\38_Isut.cfg:482
msgid "East: Oof's Fortress"
msgstr ""

#. [message], speaker=narrator
#: .\scenarios\chapter5\38_Isut.cfg:500
msgid ""
"East: Oof's Fortress, The Scavenger’s Trading Post\n"
"West: Eastern Swamp"
msgstr ""

#. [message], speaker=narrator
#: .\scenarios\chapter5\38_Isut.cfg:519
msgid ""
"North: Oof's Fortress\n"
"South: The Scavenger’s Trading Post"
msgstr ""

#. [message], speaker=second_unit
#: .\scenarios\chapter5\38_Isut.cfg:541
msgid "That wolf looks weird."
msgstr ""

#. [message], speaker=second_unit
#: .\scenarios\chapter5\38_Isut.cfg:545
msgid ""
"It looks as if it was possessed. Or rather as if something was wearing a wolf"
" like a costume."
msgstr ""

#. [message], speaker=Isut
#: .\scenarios\chapter5\38_Isut.cfg:577
msgid ""
"Finally, adversaries to match up to myself. I thought I would die from "
"boredom fighting those pathetic legionaries."
msgstr ""

#. [message], speaker=Isut
#: .\scenarios\chapter5\38_Isut.cfg:581
msgid "We will see if you make better adversaries than the other humans."
msgstr ""

#. [message], speaker=Io
#: .\scenarios\chapter5\38_Isut.cfg:605
msgid "Well, looks like we are trapped. Not like we could flee anyway."
msgstr ""

#. [message], speaker=Io
#: .\scenarios\chapter5\38_Isut.cfg:609
msgid "Fight!"
msgstr ""

#. [message], speaker=Io
#: .\scenarios\chapter5\38_Isut.cfg:634
msgid "We did it! Isut is no more!"
msgstr ""

#. [message], speaker=Io
#: .\scenarios\chapter5\38_Isut.cfg:647
msgid "Aren't his undead supposed to fall into dust or something?"
msgstr ""

#. [message]
#: .\scenarios\chapter5\38_Isut.cfg:651
msgid "They should be. But I am not versed in ock necromancy so I could be wrong."
msgstr ""

#. [message]
#: .\scenarios\chapter5\38_Isut.cfg:655
#: .\scenarios\chapter5\38_Isut.cfg:695
msgid ""
"They seem to wander aimlessly now at least, which means the fortress should "
"be safe."
msgstr ""

#. [message], speaker=Io
#: .\scenarios\chapter5\38_Isut.cfg:659
#: .\scenarios\chapter5\38_Isut.cfg:673
msgid "So, we did it?! We saved the fortress?! Hurray!"
msgstr ""

#. [message], speaker=Teumiuxe, Csia
#: .\scenarios\chapter5\38_Isut.cfg:663
#: .\scenarios\chapter5\38_Isut.cfg:677
msgid "We should go there to meet Captain Soimaql now."
msgstr ""

#. [message], speaker=Io
#: .\scenarios\chapter5\38_Isut.cfg:667
msgid "Shouldn't we kill the remaining undead before?"
msgstr ""

#. [message], speaker=Io
#: .\scenarios\chapter5\38_Isut.cfg:687
msgid "Aren't Isut undead supposed to have fallen into dust or something?"
msgstr ""

#. [message]
#: .\scenarios\chapter5\38_Isut.cfg:691
msgid "They should have. But I am not versed in ock necromancy so I could be wrong."
msgstr ""

#. [message], speaker=Io
#: .\scenarios\chapter5\38_Isut.cfg:699
msgid "We should probably kill the remain undead anyway."
msgstr ""

#. [message], speaker=unit
#: .\scenarios\chapter5\38_Isut.cfg:716
msgid "I found something in the house."
msgstr ""

#. [message], speaker=Ubidaiubua
#: .\scenarios\chapter5\38_Isut.cfg:754
msgid "I'm Ubidaiubua, a roving mage and a Traveler."
msgstr ""

#. [message], speaker=Ubidaiubua
#: .\scenarios\chapter5\38_Isut.cfg:769
msgid ""
"Thoze foolz couldn’t even recognize their mother…I’ve an exzellent magic "
"againzt the Ockz but thoze bloody legionariez don’t truzt me under the "
"pretext that I’m a Traveler, a ztranger!"
msgstr ""

#. [message], speaker=Ubidaiubua
#: .\scenarios\chapter5\38_Isut.cfg:773
msgid "My couzin Bta is captive inside. I must make sure she’z alright."
msgstr ""

#. [message], speaker=Ubidaiubua
#: .\scenarios\chapter5\38_Isut.cfg:792
msgid "Maybe they will let me in if I’m with you… "
msgstr ""

#. [message], speaker=Ubidaiubua
#: .\scenarios\chapter5\38_Isut.cfg:796
msgid "I’m willing to zell my zpells to YOU, for 78000."
msgstr ""

#. [message], speaker=Ubidaiubua
#: .\scenarios\chapter5\38_Isut.cfg:800
msgid "Deal?"
msgstr ""

#. [option]
#: .\scenarios\chapter5\38_Isut.cfg:802
msgid "Deal."
msgstr ""

#. [message], speaker=Ubidaiubua
#: .\scenarios\chapter5\38_Isut.cfg:812
msgid "I am afraid you don't have enough gold for a mage like me."
msgstr ""

#. [message], speaker=Ubidaiubua
#: .\scenarios\chapter5\38_Isut.cfg:835
msgid "I am zorry, but you zeem to be quite a party already."
msgstr ""

#. [message], speaker=Ubidaiubua
#: .\scenarios\chapter5\38_Isut.cfg:856
msgid "Ubidaiubua will remember you, pal! Thiz iz a promize!"
msgstr ""

#. [message], speaker=Ubidaiubua
#: .\scenarios\chapter5\38_Isut.cfg:860
msgid "Let’z go in the fortrezz together and zee what thre’z to zee!"
msgstr ""

#. [message], speaker=narrator
#: .\scenarios\chapter5\38_Isut.cfg:864
msgid "You can now recruit red mages."
msgstr ""

#. [message], speaker=Ubidaiubua
#: .\scenarios\chapter5\38_Isut.cfg:877
msgid "Then, leave. You don’t trust Ubidaiubua."
msgstr ""

#. [message], speaker=Ubidaiubua
#: .\scenarios\chapter5\38_Isut.cfg:881
msgid "You’re not worthy of the zervicez of the wonderful roving mage I am."
msgstr ""

#. [message], speaker=unit
#: .\scenarios\chapter5\38_Isut.cfg:917
msgid "Here is the fortress. Let's meet Captain Soimaql."
msgstr ""

#. [message], speaker=unit
#: .\scenarios\chapter5\38_Isut.cfg:954
msgid "I think it was the last undead around."
msgstr ""

#. [message], speaker=Io
#: .\scenarios\chapter5\38_Isut.cfg:958
msgid "Let's go to the fortress then."
msgstr ""

#. [message], speaker=Io
#: .\scenarios\chapter5\38_Isut.cfg:1054
msgid "No! We arrive too late; the fortress has already fallen!"
msgstr ""

#. [scenario], id=39_Oofs_Fortress
#: .\scenarios\chapter6\39_Oofs_Fortress.cfg:4
msgid "Oof's Fortress"
msgstr ""

#. [part]
#: .\scenarios\chapter6\39_Oofs_Fortress.cfg:16
msgid ""
"The greatest threat for Oof’s fortress disappeared with Isut death, but the "
"serious danger of the reappearance of this ancient malevolent spirit "
"seriously torments our hero."
msgstr ""

#. [objective], condition=win
#: .\scenarios\chapter6\39_Oofs_Fortress.cfg:37
msgid "Talk to Captain Soimaql"
msgstr ""

#. [objective], condition=win
#: .\scenarios\chapter6\39_Oofs_Fortress.cfg:47
msgid "Leave Oof's fortress for the Hall of Skulls"
msgstr ""

#. [unit], id=Soimaql, type=General
#: .\scenarios\chapter6\39_Oofs_Fortress.cfg:103
msgid "Captain Soimaql"
msgstr ""

#. [message], speaker=Io
#: .\scenarios\chapter6\39_Oofs_Fortress.cfg:201
msgid "Oof's fortress, finally."
msgstr ""

#. [message], speaker=Io
#: .\scenarios\chapter6\39_Oofs_Fortress.cfg:205
msgid "It looks like it had a bad day. Probably more like a bad week."
msgstr ""

#. [message], speaker=Io
#: .\scenarios\chapter6\39_Oofs_Fortress.cfg:209
msgid ""
"Let's try to talk with Captain Soimaql and resupply before continuing to "
"Idaamub's castle."
msgstr ""

#. [message], speaker=unit
#: .\scenarios\chapter6\39_Oofs_Fortress.cfg:223
msgid "Excuse me, are you Captain Soimaql?"
msgstr ""

#. [message], speaker=Soimaql
#: .\scenarios\chapter6\39_Oofs_Fortress.cfg:227
msgid ""
"I am. Thank you for saving what is left of the Legion that was defending the "
"fortress."
msgstr ""

#. [option]
#: .\scenarios\chapter6\39_Oofs_Fortress.cfg:244
msgid "What is the status of the fortress?"
msgstr ""

#. [message], speaker=Soimaql
#: .\scenarios\chapter6\39_Oofs_Fortress.cfg:248
msgid ""
"One hundred and eighty-two dead… And all this because a dummy disobeyed "
"orders!"
msgstr ""

#. [message], speaker=Soimaql
#: .\scenarios\chapter6\39_Oofs_Fortress.cfg:256
msgid ""
"A scout had noticed the Ocks in the wood several weeks ago, but he kept quiet"
" from fear that the others may accuse him of seeing ghosts."
msgstr ""

#. [message], speaker=Io
#: .\scenarios\chapter6\39_Oofs_Fortress.cfg:260
msgid "The Ocks?! Ain't they supposed to be all dead and buried for centuries?"
msgstr ""

#. [message], speaker=Soimaql
#: .\scenarios\chapter6\39_Oofs_Fortress.cfg:264
msgid ""
"Everybody believed those creatures had well and truly disappeared for three "
"centuries."
msgstr ""

#. [message], speaker=Soimaql
#: .\scenarios\chapter6\39_Oofs_Fortress.cfg:268
msgid ""
"What’s for sure is that the Dunefolk that are helping the Ocks have nothing "
"of specters."
msgstr ""

#. [message], speaker=Io
#: .\scenarios\chapter6\39_Oofs_Fortress.cfg:272
msgid "The Dunefolk?! Ain't they supposed to be our allies?"
msgstr ""

#. [message], speaker=Soimaql
#: .\scenarios\chapter6\39_Oofs_Fortress.cfg:276
msgid "So were the orcs not so long ago."
msgstr ""

#. [message], speaker=Soimaql
#: .\scenarios\chapter6\39_Oofs_Fortress.cfg:291
msgid ""
"If we take the Dunefolk village east, we will have half-won. \n"
"We once again broke our teeth on the western Dunefolk village, but you can "
"deal with it, if you want."
msgstr ""

#. [message], speaker=Io
#: .\scenarios\chapter6\39_Oofs_Fortress.cfg:296
msgid "We will do what we can. We need to go east to Idaamub castle anyway."
msgstr ""

#. [message], speaker=narrator
#: .\scenarios\chapter6\39_Oofs_Fortress.cfg:328
msgid ""
"West: Eastern Swamp, The Scavenger's Trading Post\n"
"East: Hall of Skulls, Fire Cliffs, Idaamub's Castle"
msgstr ""

#. [message]
#: .\scenarios\chapter6\39_Oofs_Fortress.cfg:346
msgid ""
"I was getting tired of smashing their heads all day long. They might calm "
"down now that this Isut crawler is gone."
msgstr ""

#. [message]
#: .\scenarios\chapter6\39_Oofs_Fortress.cfg:360
msgid "Go see captain Soimaql. Whatever intel you've got, he will be interested."
msgstr ""

#. [message]
#: .\scenarios\chapter6\39_Oofs_Fortress.cfg:374
msgid ""
"Congrats on how you dealt with that Isut necromancer. He had been spreading "
"terror in the region for several days. "
msgstr ""

#. [message]
#: .\scenarios\chapter6\39_Oofs_Fortress.cfg:378
msgid ""
"Since last battle, he kept challenging us to a duel. We would have been crazy"
" to accept."
msgstr ""

#. [message]
#: .\scenarios\chapter6\39_Oofs_Fortress.cfg:392
msgid ""
"Shh! 'm waitin' fo' 'nother skull t'pop out of da moat, like they kept doin' "
"da whole day."
msgstr ""

#. [message]
#: .\scenarios\chapter6\39_Oofs_Fortress.cfg:396
msgid ""
"I dunno if I keep shootin' da same guy 'n' he keeps gettin' back up all da "
"time or if there's lotta them in there."
msgstr ""

#. [message]
#: .\scenarios\chapter6\39_Oofs_Fortress.cfg:410
msgid ""
"I don't know if those undead are dead for good, but anyway, you did a good "
"job. Maybe I will finally be able to sleep a bit."
msgstr ""

#. [message]
#: .\scenarios\chapter6\39_Oofs_Fortress.cfg:424
msgid ""
"Talkin' 'bout gratitude, da sergeant confiscated ma beer when I told him I "
"saw the Ocks, 'n' when I talked 'bout it t'Soimaql, he assigned me t'fire "
"prevention fo' a week.  I should rather've kept it closed."
msgstr ""

#. [message]
#: .\scenarios\chapter6\39_Oofs_Fortress.cfg:428
msgid "Anyway, if Isut's no Ock, I dunno what he's."
msgstr ""

#. [message]
#: .\scenarios\chapter6\39_Oofs_Fortress.cfg:442
msgid ""
"I was ordered not to let anyone disturb the injured. Do quickly what you have"
" to do with the mage or I will bawl you out."
msgstr ""

#. [message]
#: .\scenarios\chapter6\39_Oofs_Fortress.cfg:456
msgid ""
"I sometimes wonder why I exhaust myself healing the injured. I put them back "
"on their feet, and they come back to me in an even more deplorable state."
msgstr ""

#. [message]
#: .\scenarios\chapter6\39_Oofs_Fortress.cfg:460
msgid ""
" I have a few potions that could heal you, as well as a few magical trinkets "
"taken to the enemy. "
msgstr ""

#. [message], speaker=trader
#: .\scenarios\chapter6\39_Oofs_Fortress.cfg:503
msgid "Take what interests you, but be quick! I have other things to do!"
msgstr ""

