#. [message], speaker=Io
#: .\scenarios\chapter6\43_Western_Village.cfg:1236
msgid "My friends, we have defeated the Dunefolk. That's a great victory."
msgstr ""

#. [message], speaker=Io
#: .\scenarios\chapter6\43_Western_Village.cfg:1240
msgid ""
"We have also learnt what the Ocks will do next, which means we have a chance "
"to stop them."
msgstr ""

#. [message], speaker=Io
#: .\scenarios\chapter6\43_Western_Village.cfg:1244
msgid ""
"To do so, we now have to travel to Idaamub's castle, which was our "
"destination anyway, and find out where this mysterious secret room is."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=Ancient Dark Wose LoI, race=wose
#: .\units\Ancient_Dark_Wose.cfg:4
msgid "Ancient Dark Wose"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=Ancient Dark Wose LoI, race=wose
#: .\units\Ancient_Dark_Wose.cfg:16
msgid ""
"It has always been all too known to all creatures that nature is not only a "
"nurturing mother; it can also be cruel, violent and destructive. It's unknown"
" what makes a wose become corrupted, but one thing is certain: nowhere else "
"does nature's rage becomes more evident than in an Ancient Dark Wose."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=Fury Scourge LoI, race=demon-loti, gender=female
#: .\units\d3_Medusa_Witch.cfg:4
msgid "Fury Scourge"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=Fury Scourge LoI, race=demon-loti, gender=female
#: .\units\d3_Medusa_Witch.cfg:18
msgid ""
"Fury Scourge are juvenile Furies. Although not as deadly as their adult form,"
" they can still petrify those who dare look at them."
msgstr ""

#. [attack], type=cold, range=ranged
#: .\units\d3_Medusa_Witch.cfg:57
#: .\units\d3_Medusa_Witch.cfg:71
#: .\units\Fury.cfg:87
#: .\units\Fury.cfg:101
msgid "petrify"
msgstr ""

#. [petrifies]
#: .\units\d3_Medusa_Witch.cfg:81
msgid ""
"Petrify:\n"
"This attack petrifies the target, turning it to stone. Units that have been "
"petrified may not move or attack. The effect will wear off after a turn."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=Deshra Juggernaut LoI, race=deshra
#: .\units\deshra_juggernaut.cfg:5
msgid "Deshra Juggernaut"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=Direrat LoI, race=monster
#: .\units\Direrat.cfg:4
msgid "Direrat"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=Direrat LoI, race=monster
#: .\units\Direrat.cfg:19
msgid ""
"Much larger than the giant rats which often inhabit caves, these vermin can "
"injure an armed civilian, and can prove frustratingly aggressive on any "
"footing. On top of being notably very aggressive at night, these creatures "
"pose much of a threat to any serious fighter."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=Gobot Dragonguard LoI, race=steelhive
#: .\units\Dragonguard.cfg:4
msgid "Gobot Dragonguard"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=Gobot Dragonguard LoI, race=steelhive
#: .\units\Dragonguard.cfg:18
msgid ""
"It is not clear why the Dragonguards are called what they are, a name stolen "
"from the dwarves. Some speculate that the name comes from their weapon of "
"choice, these strange staves that belch fire and death. Others have surmised "
"that it is because such weapons would be a threat against even a true Dragon,"
" should such a thing be seen again in the known world. Whatever the case, it "
"is for these weapons that the guardians of the great Goblin citadels are both"
" renowned and feared; weapons that have broken the mightiest of warriors with"
" a storm of blows."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=Dreadscale LoI, race=monster
#: .\units\dreadscale.cfg:51
msgid "Dreadscale"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=Elder Dark Wose LoI, race=wose
#: .\units\Elder_Dark_Wose.cfg:4
msgid "Elder Dark Wose"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=Elder Dark Wose LoI, race=wose
#: .\units\Elder_Dark_Wose.cfg:16
msgid ""
"Filled with hatred and malice, these beings will destroy anything that is "
"foolish enough to stand in their way."
msgstr ""

#. [race], id=deshra
#: .\units\factions.cfg:4
msgid "race^Deshra"
msgstr ""

#. [race], id=deshra
#: .\units\factions.cfg:5
msgid "race+female^Deshra"
msgstr ""

#. [race], id=deshra
#: .\units\factions.cfg:6
msgid "race^Deshrai"
msgstr ""

#. [race], id=deshra
#: .\units\factions.cfg:12
msgid "The Deshra (literally "
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=Frozen Lich LoI, race=undead
#: .\units\Frozen_Lich.cfg:4
msgid "Frozen Lich"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=Frozen Lich LoI, race=undead
#: .\units\Frozen_Lich.cfg:29
msgid ""
"A lich is the physical embodiment of black magic’s first goal: the quest to "
"achieve immortality. Though a great deal is sacrificed in the rebirth, in "
"becoming a lich, one cheats death of that which truly gives it terror. For it"
" is the mind that is retained, and the spirit which follows, though the body "
"may wither away.\n"
"\n"
"It is not known, save perhaps by the inner circles of necromancy, whether "
"life is prolonged indefinitely or simply extended. The fact that this "
"question can be raised at all is a testament to the magnitude of what their "
"order has achieved.\n"
"\n"
"This lich transformed in the Ice Cave, conferring it special powers based on "
"cold."
msgstr ""

#. [attack], type=cold, range=melee
#: .\units\Frozen_Lich.cfg:45
msgid "cold touch"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=Fury LoI, race=demon-loti, gender=female
#: .\units\Fury.cfg:18
msgid ""
"Furies were once very beautiful beings, legend said that a man who looked at "
"them was not able to keep a clear mind because of their beauty. But when they"
" turned against the gods they were cursed and turned into monstrosities. "
"Their gaze is so terrible that any being looking at them will be paralyzed in"
" fear. They are surrounded by a dark aura that weakens and kills enemies."
msgstr ""

#. [attack], type=arcane, range=ranged
#: .\units\Fury.cfg:73
msgid "gaze"
msgstr ""

#. [petrifies]
#: .\units\Fury.cfg:111
msgid ""
"Petrify:\n"
"This attack petrifies the target, turning it to stone. Units that have been "
"petrified may not move or attack. It will wear off after a turn."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=Green Crystal LoI, race=abstraction
#: .\units\Green_Crystal.cfg:5
msgid "Green Crystal"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=Green Crystal LoI, race=abstraction
#: .\units\Green_Crystal.cfg:31
msgid ""
"A Green Crystal is a Shard that has emerged from a high concentration of mana"
" located in a cave.\n"
"\n"
"Crystals are bound to their mana geyser, so they cannot go out of the cave "
"they were born in. Crystals are crystalline in nature and so have unusual "
"resistances. A consequence of this is their immunity to Drain, Poison and "
"Plague."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=Gobot Grenadeer LoI, race=steelhive
#: .\units\Grenadeer.cfg:4
msgid "Gobot Grenadeer"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=Gobot Grenadeer LoI, race=steelhive
#: .\units\Grenadeer.cfg:18
msgid ""
"This curious machine looks like a Dwarven Thunderguards made out of metal. "
"The Dwarven Thunderguards are famed for their curious weaponry, these strange"
" staves of wood and iron that make a thunderous noise in their anger. The "
"machinations behind this weaponry are a mystery, a secret taken to the grave "
"by the dwarves of Knalga who wield them, and are assumed to have even forged "
"them. The most that is known are reports of dwarves pouring a strange black "
"dust into the mouth of their weapons, which some say is a food to fuel the "
"beast imprisoned within. It seems that goblins tried to replicate them, "
"leading to a strange machine able to shoot explosive spheres.\n"
"\n"
"Though a single shot from these ‘boomsticks’ can take several minutes to "
"prepare, the results are seen by the goblins as being well worth the wait."
msgstr ""

#. [attack], type=fire, range=ranged
#: .\units\Grenadeer.cfg:29
msgid "boomstick"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=Hell Boar LoI, race=monster
#: .\units\Hellboar.cfg:4
msgid "Hell Boar"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=Hell Boar LoI, race=monster
#: .\units\Hellboar.cfg:25
msgid ""
"It is said that those boars were bread by the Ocks to be used as yoke for "
"their wagons. Since those were vanquished, they found a place of residence in"
" the Black Forest, where they compete with bears for food."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=Diseased Herb Spirit LoI, race=wose
#: .\units\HerbDiseased.cfg:5
msgid "Diseased Herb Spirit"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=Diseased Herb Spirit LoI, race=wose
#: .\units\HerbDiseased.cfg:18
msgid ""
"Most of the herb spirits use their power to repel insect infestations but a "
"few of them welcome the insects in so that they can use them as game pieces "
"or suddenly expel them as a method of attack."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=Ice Bat LoI, race=elemental
#: .\units\Ice_Bat.cfg:4
msgid "Ice Bat"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=Ice Bat LoI, race=elemental
#: .\units\Ice_Bat.cfg:20
msgid ""
"The most vicious, predatory, and successful of the creatures born in the ice "
"cave."
msgstr ""

#. [attack], type=blade, range=melee
#: .\units\Ice_Bat.cfg:37
msgid "ice fangs"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=Ice Bowman LoI, race=elemental, gender=male
#: .\units\Ice_Bowman.cfg:4
msgid "Ice Bowman"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=Ice Bowman LoI, race=elemental, gender=male
#: .\units\Ice_Bowman.cfg:18
msgid ""
"Born in the cold of the ice cave, ice bowmen are fearsome enemies. The great "
"strength allows them to attack with high range and power."
msgstr ""

#. [attack], type=pierce, range=ranged
#: .\units\Ice_Bowman.cfg:37
#: .\units\Ice_Master_Bowman.cfg:37
msgid "ice longbow"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=Ice Golem LoI, race=elemental
#: .\units\Ice_Golem.cfg:5
msgid "Ice Golem"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=Ice Golem LoI, race=elemental
#: .\units\Ice_Golem.cfg:31
msgid ""
"Ice elementals, once gathering enough elemental essence, can absorb more ice "
"and grow larger and stronger. Although they are weak, they can take massive "
"amounts of damage before they are destroyed to shards."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=Ice Guard LoI, race=elemental
#: .\units\Ice_Guard.cfg:4
msgid "Ice Guard"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=Ice Guard LoI, race=elemental
#: .\units\Ice_Guard.cfg:18
msgid ""
"Ice Guards are picked from the best swordsmen in the ice cave. They function "
"as bodyguards and commanders. Their reliability and mastery of close combat "
"are their best assets, for which they are well-renowned."
msgstr ""

#. [attack], type=blade, range=melee
#: .\units\Ice_Guard.cfg:39
msgid "ice longsword"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=Ice Troll Hero LoI, race=troll
#: .\units\Ice_Hero.cfg:4
msgid "Ice Troll Hero"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=Ice Troll Hero LoI, race=troll
#: .\units\Ice_Hero.cfg:16
msgid ""
"Some ice trolls are born with an exceptional share of the strength and "
"vitality that characterizes their race. In a society where might makes right,"
" those of their ilk revere them as heroes."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=Ice Master Bowman LoI, race=human, gender=male
#: .\units\Ice_Master_Bowman.cfg:4
msgid "Ice Master Bowman"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=Ice Master Bowman LoI, race=human, gender=male
#: .\units\Ice_Master_Bowman.cfg:32
msgid ""
"Born in the cold of the ice cave, ice master bowmen have reached the zenith "
"of their art, inasmuch as any ice bowman is capable. Armed with a great ice "
"bow, these warriors crown battalions of ice bowmen with their presence, "
"bringing down many a foe with their well-aimed shots. Of the many races in "
"the world, only the elves surpass them in archery, and their human "
"counterparts have speculated, perhaps in envy, that this is only by dint of "
"age."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=Ice Swordsman LoI, race=elemental
#: .\units\Ice_Swordsman.cfg:4
msgid "Ice Swordsman"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=Ice Swordsman LoI, race=elemental
#: .\units\Ice_Swordsman.cfg:17
msgid ""
"Born into the cold of the ice cave, this unit is an experienced warrior "
"equipped with a sturdy broadsword made of ice."
msgstr ""

#. [attack], type=blade, range=melee
#: .\units\Ice_Swordsman.cfg:38
msgid "ice sword"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=Ice Troll LoI, race=troll
#: .\units\Ice_Troll.cfg:4
msgid "Ice Troll"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=Ice Troll LoI, race=troll
#: .\units\Ice_Troll.cfg:16
msgid ""
"Ice trolls are been recently discovered. It is thought that they evolved from"
" common trolls trapped in a region of freezing cold. A fully-grown ice troll "
"towers above a man, and, even unarmed, would be a great threat in combat. The"
" large clubs typically favored in fighting act as extensions of their arms, "
"used for the same purpose of mauling their prey into submission."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=Ice Troll Shaman LoI, race=troll
#: .\units\Ice_Troll_Shaman.cfg:4
msgid "Ice Troll Shaman"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=Ice Troll Shaman LoI, race=troll
#: .\units\Ice_Troll_Shaman.cfg:33
msgid ""
"Ice trolls are been recently discovered. It is thought that they evolved from"
" common trolls trapped in a region of freezing cold. Ice troll shamans are "
"the mystical leaders of the ice trolls. Though not as strong or tough as "
"other ice trolls, their true power lies in their cold magic, which they use "
"to blast enemies with gouts of ice or to hide in the frozen forests."
msgstr ""

#. [attack], type=cold, range=ranged
#: .\units\Ice_Troll_Shaman.cfg:50
msgid "ice blast"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=Ice Troll Warrior LoI, race=troll
#: .\units\Ice_Warrior.cfg:4
msgid "Ice Troll Warrior"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=Ice Troll Warrior LoI, race=troll
#: .\units\Ice_Warrior.cfg:28
msgid ""
"Ice trolls are been recently discovered. It is thought that they evolved from"
" common trolls trapped in a region of freezing cold. Ice trolls typically "
"neither need nor prefer to use any proper armament in combat, as large "
"‘sticks and stones’ serve them all too well. However, ice trolls have been "
"seen on numerous occasions clad in rough-shod armor and bearing metal "
"hammers. It is speculated that orcish allies are the source and crafters of "
"these; expeditions into several forcibly-vacated ice troll caves have shown "
"little evidence of tool use, and certainly no metalworking of any kind. Given"
" how dangerous an ice troll is with its bare hands, the thought of one with "
"proper armament is entirely unsettling."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=Ice Wyvern LoI, race=elemental
#: .\units\Ice_Wyvern.cfg:8
msgid "Ice Wyvern"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=Ice Wyvern LoI, race=elemental
#: .\units\Ice_Wyvern.cfg:49
msgid ""
"Wyverns are large reptiles that resemble dragons, but are not the "
"intelligent, magical creatures. However, the fact that they are just wild "
"beasts should not cause any traveler who encounters one to dismiss the "
"threat, for they are fast and fierce when threatened or hungry.\n"
"\n"
"Although wyverns are social creatures, usually traveling in pairs or small "
"groups, their icy counterpart seems to be of solitary nature. Their hunting "
"patterns and diet are difficult to discern, for they often work with smaller "
"animals that would appear to be potential prey. That odd behavior may be an "
"adaptation to the harsh icy environments they inhabit."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=Initiate, race=human
#: .\units\Mage_Initiate.cfg:5
msgid "Initiate"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=Initiate, race=human
#: .\units\Mage_Initiate.cfg:19
msgid ""
"Initiates belong to the few individuals who are capable of using magic and "
"who had the luck of being discovered by a mage order. The amount of studying "
"that is still ahead of them may seem intimidating, but at the same time, the "
"mere existence of this knowledge is a testament to what humanity can achieve.\n"
"\n"
"Initiates are helpless in melee combat, but possess great offensive potential"
" that will grow as they get more experienced."
msgstr ""

#. [female]
#: .\units\Mage_Initiate.cfg:77
msgid "female^Initiate"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=Saurian Matriarch LoI, race=lizard, gender=female
#: .\units\Matriarch.cfg:4
msgid "female^Saurian Matriarch"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=Mehsi LoI, race=monster
#: .\units\Mehsi.cfg:4
msgid "Mehsi"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=Mehsi LoI, race=monster
#: .\units\Mehsi.cfg:22
msgid ""
"Mehsi incite fear and awe in miners and explorers, figuring often in folklore"
" as wrathful deities of the underground. Capable of destroying carts "
"effortlessly, and possessed of seemingly endless strength and vitality, these"
" elusive leviathans are destructive and relentless to any who try to combat "
"them. Generally living in the deep, Mehsi are imposing even to the elite "
"dwarven warriors, and are the reason they seldom inhabit tunnels close to the"
" surface."
msgstr ""

#. [hides], id=dig
#: .\units\Mehsi.cfg:28
#: .\units\Mine_Worm.cfg:41
msgid "dig"
msgstr ""

#. [hides], id=dig
#: .\units\Mehsi.cfg:29
#: .\units\Mine_Worm.cfg:42
msgid "female^dig"
msgstr ""

#. [hides], id=dig
#: .\units\Mehsi.cfg:30
#: .\units\Mine_Worm.cfg:43
msgid ""
"This unit can hide underground, and remain undetected by its enemies.\n"
"\n"
"Enemy units cannot see this unit while it is underground, except if they have"
" units next to it. Any enemy unit that first discovers this unit immediately "
"loses all its remaining movement."
msgstr ""

#. [hides], id=dig
#: .\units\Mehsi.cfg:33
#: .\units\Mine_Worm.cfg:46
msgid ""
"On soft ground, this unit’s ambush skill renders it invisible to enemies "
"unless it is immediately adjacent or has revealed itself by attacking."
msgstr ""

#. [attack], type=pierce, range=ranged
#: .\units\Mehsi.cfg:44
#: .\units\Mine_Worm.cfg:57
msgid "stings"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=Mine Worm LoI, race=monster
#: .\units\Mine_Worm.cfg:4
msgid "Mine Worm"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=Mine Worm LoI, race=monster
#: .\units\Mine_Worm.cfg:35
msgid ""
"Scholars differ as to the ancestry of the Mine Worm. Some hold that they were"
" brought to the mine by the demons. Others hold that they have always been "
"here. What is certain is that it is wise to avoid mines where they are known "
"to congregate."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=Ice Hole LoI, race=elemental
#: .\units\Pseudo_units.cfg:4
msgid "Ice Hole"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=Ice Monolith Sword, race=elemental
#: .\units\Pseudo_units.cfg:82
msgid "Ice Monolith Sword"
msgstr ""

#. [message], speaker=second_unit
#: .\units\Pseudo_units.cfg:128
msgid "What the hell! That block of ice just turned into a swordsman."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=Ice Monolith Bow, race=elemental
#: .\units\Pseudo_units.cfg:161
msgid "Ice Monolith Bow"
msgstr ""

#. [message], speaker=second_unit
#: .\units\Pseudo_units.cfg:207
msgid "Great... Now there are ice blocks turning into archers too."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=Purple Crystal LoI, race=abstraction
#: .\units\Purple_Crystal.cfg:5
msgid "Purple Crystal"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=Purple Crystal LoI, race=abstraction
#: .\units\Purple_Crystal.cfg:31
msgid ""
"When too much mana concentrates in one place, a Purple Crystal natural "
"emerge. It is a sudden event, very different from the slow accumulation of "
"mana whose result is Green Crystals. \n"
"\n"
"Crystals are bound to their mana geyser, so they cannot go out of the cave "
"they were born in. Crystals are crystalline in nature and so have unusual "
"resistances. A consequence of this is their immunity to Drain, Poison and "
"Plague."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=Scorpion Soldier LoI, race=monster
#: .\units\Scorpion_Soldier.cfg:4
msgid "Scorpion Soldier"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=Scorpion Soldier LoI, race=monster
#: .\units\Scorpion_Soldier.cfg:19
msgid ""
"A giant scorpion is highly dangerous. The deadliness of this one is beyond "
"imagination."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=Spiderling LoI, race=monster
#: .\units\Spiderling.cfg:4
msgid "Spiderling"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=Spiderling LoI, race=monster
#: .\units\Spiderling.cfg:22
msgid ""
"Right after their birth, Giant Spiders, then called Spiderling, already have "
"a decent span, comparable in size to a Giant Scorpion. Although far less "
"dangerous than their adult form, they can already be a threat to surprised "
"adventurers due to their poisonous bite and their thick, sticky web."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=Tesla Coil LoI, race=monster
#: .\units\Tesla_Coil.cfg:5
msgid "Tesla Coil"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=Tesla Coil LoI, race=monster
#: .\units\Tesla_Coil.cfg:36
msgid ""
"High amounts of an unknown kind of energy are created in this machine, and "
"used in an unknown way somewhere else. You have pretty much no idea what this"
" thing is meant to do. The light it creates seems to harm everyone nearby."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=Gobot Thunderguard LoI, race=steelhive
#: .\units\Thunderguard.cfg:4
msgid "Gobot Thunderguard"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=Gobot Thunderguard LoI, race=steelhive
#: .\units\Thunderguard.cfg:18
msgid ""
"This curious machine looks like a Dwarven Thunderguards made out of metal. "
"The Dwarven Thunderguards are famed for their curious weaponry, these strange"
" staves of wood and iron that make a thunderous noise in their anger. The "
"machinations behind this weaponry are a mystery, a secret taken to the grave "
"by the dwarves of Knalga who wield them, and are assumed to have even forged "
"them. The most that is known are reports of dwarves pouring a strange black "
"dust into the mouth of their weapons, which some say is a food to fuel the "
"beast imprisoned within. It seems that goblins tried to replicate them, "
"leading to a strange machine able to shoot lightnings.\n"
"\n"
"Though a single shot from these ‘thundersticks’ can take several minutes to "
"prepare, the results are seen by the goblins as being well worth the wait."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=Young Man LoI, race=human, gender=male
#: .\units\Young_Man.cfg:4
msgid "Young Man"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=Young Man LoI, race=human, gender=male
#: .\units\Young_Man.cfg:17
msgid ""
"This Young Man has decided to go on an adventure. He was not trained to use "
"any weapon but is smart enough to understand how to use them. He can use "
"pitchforks, clubs, daggers and bows, but only one at a time. "
msgstr ""

#. [attack], type=blade, range=melee
#: .\units\Young_Man.cfg:91
msgid "knife"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=Young Giant Spider LoI, race=monster
#: .\units\Young_Spider.cfg:4
msgid "Young Giant Spider"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=Young Giant Spider LoI, race=monster
#: .\units\Young_Spider.cfg:22
msgid ""
"Although the most encounter version is its adult form, Giant Spider are not "
"born directly as such. When they are born, they are called Spiderlings and "
"have a size similar to Giant Scorpions. They then metamorphose a first time "
"to become what we call Young Giant Spiders, that are twice the size of the "
"Spiderling, then a second time to become Giant Spiders. Although its younger "
"version tends to hide from sight, it is a formidable opponent that should not"
" be taken lightly."
msgstr ""

